New Caledonia: 15 More Dengue Fever Cases Reported
--------------------------------------------------
Authorities in New Caledonia have confirmed another 15 cases of dengue
fever in the French Pacific territory. Local media reports say there have
now been almost 60 new cases of the potentially fatal mosquito-borne
disease since the beginning of 2003. Last month, health authorities
identified the beginning of an epidemic and stepped up a campaign to fight
the disease.
Dengue fever outbreaks have also been reported recently from Vanuatu, Fiji,
and the French territory of Wallis and Futuna [see: Dengue/DHF update 2003
(04) 20030130.0262].
