Bolivia (Cochabamba): First Deaths in Dengue Outbreak - DHF or YF?
------------------------------------------------
Yesterday, a man and wife died in Eterazama, Chapare, with symptoms of
either dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) or yellow fever (YF). The laboratory
report is pending. A similar case, a male aged 20 years from Eterazama, was
admitted to the Villa Tunari Hospital on 29 Jan 2003 and died on 4 Feb 2003.
His wife, aged 18 years, had died at home on 18 Jan 2003 with the same
symptoms. She had been attended by a private doctor. These were the first
deaths in the dengue epidemic that began in the Cochabamba region on 4 Nov
2002. So far Cochabamba town has had 29 confirmed cases of dengue fever,
including one of DHF, who is recovering.
The zone of Eterazama has so far reported most cases of dengue (80) in the
Cochabamba region. Samples from the fatal cases will be sent to Peru for
confirmation of dengue or yellow fever. Results should be available on Fri
14 Feb 2003.
Suspected and confirmed cases of dengue are increasing at the rate of 17
per day in Chapare, the highest rate in the country. In Santa Cruz the rate
is 15 per day and in Pando 5 per day. In 5 epidemiological weeks, Bolivia
has reported 1300 cases of dengue, including 751 in Cochabamba.
