Philippines: Increase in Dengue Cases in Zamboanga City
----------------------------------------------------
"Search and destroy," the order said. However, this order was not given to
the police or military. This was the order of city health officer Rodel
Agbulos to his fumigation team in this city because of the alarming
increase of dengue fever in barangays within a 7-km radius. These barangays
are Santa Catalina, Zone IV, Tumaga, Putik, Mercedes, Tugbungan, Tetuan,
Boalan, Canelar, and Sinunuc.
In January there were 20 cases of dengue fever that were registered in his
office, where the majority of the victims were children aged 3 to 4,
Agbulos disclosed. He also said that for the first 5 days of February 2003,
there were already 16 dengue fever cases registered from barangays Upper
Calarian, Baliwasan, Talon-Talon, and Canelar.
Agbulos ordered a search-and-destroy operation because fumigation kills
only the [adult] mosquitoes and not the larvae, which after 28 days would
hatch into another batch of the dengue virus-carrying mosquitoes. "So what
is best to do besides fumigation is to search for and destroy their
breeding places," he said.
[Byline: B. Garcia Jr.]
